works.description: In February this year, a fleet of 100 Rolls-Royce motor cars took to the streets of London to celebrate 100 years of famous Spirit of Ecstasy mascot, which first adorned the Rolls-Royce models in 1911. At that time, we introduced you to some of the most famous Rolls-Royce hood ornaments to date. Now, Rolls-Royce Motor Cars has announced the details of a special art commission in honor of the centenary of the Spirit of Ecstasy.
